net.objectzoo.delegates

Interface Action2<T1,T2>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - The type of the Action2's first parameter
    T2 - The type of the Action2's second parameter
    All Superinterfaces:
    BiConsumer<T1,T2>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Event2AsyncDelegate<T1,T2>, Event2Delegate<T1,T2>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Action2AsyncSupport, Action2ToAsyncAction2, Event2AsyncAdapter, Event2Caller, Event2Distributor
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference. 

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Action2<T1,T2>
extends BiConsumer<T1,T2>
    An Action2 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call. To enable interoperability with Java 8 libraries Action is replaceable with its super interface BiConsumer in many situations.
    Author:
    tilmann
